OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773288217
OL,3,CGovernment considering formal apology
OL,4,Cfor state's role in forced adoptions
OL,6,FFor those so grievously affected by
OL,7,Fforced adoption between the 1950s and
OL,8,F1970s, nothing can turn the clock
OL,9,Fback. But the Government's hint at an
OL,10,Fapology today is a step forward, and a
OL,11,Flong time coming for many campaigners.
OL,12,FITV News Social Affairs Correspondent
OL,13,FSarah Corker reports.
OL,15,FAn apology for the state's role in
OL,16,Fhistoric forced adoption is being
OL,17,Fconsidered by the Government, a
OL,18,Fminister said while making a
OL,19,Fsignificant admission.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
