CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773288217
OL,3,CGovernment considering formal apology
OL,4,Cfor state's role in forced adoptions
OL,6,FHe did not provide a timescale for
OL,7,Fwhen a formal apology might be issued.
OL,9,FIn 1996, Ann Keen was 17 when her son
OL,10,Fwas taken from her.
OL,12,FThe Former Labour MP, who is now a
OL,13,Ftrustee for the Movement for an
OL,14,FAdoption Apology (MAA) campaign group,
OL,15,Ftold ITV News about her experience.
OL,17,F"We were so degraded and always told
OL,18,Fwe were bad people, and that we
OL,19,Fweren't worthy of having the baby. If
OL,20,Fwe loved the baby, we would let it go
OL,21,Fand give it up for adoption."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
