OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773288217
OL,3,CGovernment considering formal apology
OL,4,Cfor state's role in forced adoptions
OL,6,FAn estimated 185,000 children were
OL,7,Ftaken from unmarried mothers and
OL,8,Fadopted between 1949 and 1976 in
OL,9,FEngland and Wales.
OL,11,FThe Welsh and Scottish governments
OL,12,Fhave previously said sorry to those
OL,13,Faffected, and campaigners have long
OL,14,Fcalled for an apology from the
OL,15,FWestminster Government.
OL,17,FDiana Defries, who was forced to give
OL,18,Fup her child at the age of 16 in 1974,
OL,19,Ftold ITV News that the admission and a
OL,20,Fformal apology are crucial.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773288217
OL,3,CGovernment considering formal apology
OL,4,Cfor state's role in forced adoptions
OL,6,F"It's very significant, and it feels
OL,7,Flike progress.
OL,9,F"A public and heartfelt apology will
OL,10,Fchange how people feel about
OL,11,Fthemselves and how society views them."
OL,13,FThe committee heard from women whose
OL,14,Fchildren were taken from them, as well
OL,15,Fas adoptees who shared their lifelong
OL,16,Ftrauma as a result of what happened to
OL,17,Fthem.
OL,19,FSally Ells said she is a "survivor of
OL,20,Fhistoric forced adoption and I live
OL,21,Fwith its lifelong consequences".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
