CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773288217
OL,3,CGovernment considering formal apology
OL,4,Cfor state's role in forced adoptions
OL,6,FIn an emotional testimony of her own
OL,7,Fexperience, the co-founder of the
OL,8,FAdult Adoptee Movement, told MPs:
OL,9,F"It's not a historic harm. It
OL,10,Fcontinues across my life and across
OL,11,Fthe lives of many, many adult
OL,12,Fadoptees."
OL,14,FShe said a "meaningful apology would
OL,15,Fcorrect that harmful narrative" that
OL,16,F"adoption saved children like me and
OL,17,Fthat we should be grateful".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
